text: Highway 14 (British Columbia Highway 14) is a highway on Vancouver Island in British Columbia. It is an east-west highway that travels between Victoria, British Columbia (east end) to Port Renfrew (west end). It is a highway that travels around the south coast of Vancouver Island. Between Victoria and Port Renfrew, there is a town called Sooke in the highway. The highway is about 98 km (60.8 miles) in length. Category:Trans-Canada Highway Category:British Columbia provincial highways
title: British Columbia Highway 14
